benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: DELETE /1.0/kb/invoiceItems/{invoiceItemId}/customFields - Remove custom fields from invoice item

covered: Valid Deletion: Successful removal across multiple configurations (empty fields, single field, or multiple fields) and with/without optional headers (TC01, TC02, TC03, TC04, TC05, TC06).
Non-Existent Resource Handling: 404 when the invoice item does not exist (TC08).
Authorization/Authentication: Missing required header (TC09) and expired/invalid token (TC19); 401 in that path.
Query Parameter Handling: Various combos including none (TC01), subset (TC02), large IDs (TC12), duplicates (TC18), extra/malformed (TC10, TC11), and long header cases (TC16, TC20).
Error Handling: Coverage of invalid UUID (TC07), missing header (TC09), and service availability issues (TC14).
Header Handling/Regression: Tests for header parsing/regression (TC16, TC20) and header presence (TC05, TC06).
Edge Cases: Deleting with zero (TC04) or one (TC03) custom field.
Performance/Load: Heavy load scenario with acceptable response time (TC13).
Data Volume: Handling 100+ customField IDs (TC12) and duplicates (TC18).
Security: Injection attempt in customField parameter (TC15).
gaps: Concurrency/Race Conditions: No tests to verify behavior under concurrent deletions.
Rate Limiting: No tests for throttling or 429 responses under load.
Caching Behavior: No tests validating ETag/Cache-Control headers on DELETE.
Soft Deletes: No explicit tests differentiating soft vs hard deletion.
403 Forbidden Scenarios: No tests specifically asserting 403 for insufficient privileges.
recommendations: Add a dedicated concurrency/race-condition test to ensure safe behavior when multiple clients attempt DELETE simultaneously.
Introduce rate-limiting/throttling tests (e.g., 429) to validate resilience under burst traffic.
Add tests for caching headers (ETag/Cache-Control) on DELETE responses if applicable.
Clarify and test soft-delete semantics (if applicable) and ensure tests reflect expected deletion type.
Add 403 Forbidden tests to cover scenarios with insufficient privileges beyond missing header/token cases.
Add explicit 500 Internal Server Error tests to complement existing 503 cases and verify robust error reporting.
